  "prompt": "How come every time I get instructions to meet someone they are never there?",
  "response": "It sounds like you're experiencing some frustration with meetings or appointments not going as planned. There could be several reasons this is happening:\n\n1. **Miscommunication:** There might be a misunderstanding about the time, date, or location. Double-check your messages or instructions and ensure you have all the correct details.\n\n2. **Changes in Plans:** The person you're supposed to meet might have had a change in plans that they didn't communicate effectively. Try confirming the meeting closer to the time to ensure everything is still on track.\n\n3. **Reliability:** If this is happening regularly with the same individuals, they might not be very reliable or organized. You might want to address the issue directly with them.\n\n4. **External Factors:** There could be external factors such as traffic, emergencies, or other unforeseen events preventing them from attending the meeting.\n\nTo mitigate these issues, here are a few tips:\n- **Confirm Details:** Send a reminder or confirmation message before the meeting.\n- **Set Clear Expectations:** Make sure both parties are on the same page regarding the meeting details.\n- **Follow Up:** If someone isn't where they\u2019re supposed to be, follow up promptly to understand what happened.\n- **Alternative Arrangements:** Have a backup plan or alternative way to meet (e.g., virtual meeting) if something goes wrong.\n\nImproving communication and planning may help reduce these occurrences in the future.",
